<body class="service-weekly">
  <a href="#main" class="visually-hidden-focusable">Skip to main content</a>
  <div id="wrapper">
    <%- include('../partials/header') %>

    <main id="main">
      <section class="hero hero-wrapper" style="background-image: url('https://images.ctfassets.net/ftcnv5up9dxv/7dX53kEhONSiR3WxVDA347/4e95c833c6b566b450951f3100d6f56f/What_You_ll_Need_to_Clean_Your_Pool.jpg')">
        <div class="title-wrapper col-sm-12">
          <h1>Weekly Service</h1>
        </div>
        <div class="link-wrapper col-sm-12">
          <a href="/contact-us" class="btn btn-lg btn-primary">Schedule Now</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="explaination-wrapper">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="row">
            <div class="left col-sm-12 col-lg-7">
              <h2 class="section-title">Weekly Pool Cleaning</h2>
              <h3>Your Weekly Service Experts</h3>
              <p>Swim Studs keeps your pool sparkling, balanced, and swim‑ready all season. Each visit includes skimming, brushing, vacuuming as needed, emptying baskets, testing and adjusting water chemistry, and a quick equipment check.</p>
              <p>Whether you run chlorine or salt, and DE, sand, or cartridge filtration, we tailor service to your system, usage, and season. On your first visit, we establish a clean, healthy baseline so maintenance is effortless.</p>
              <p><strong>Ready for effortless pool care? <a href="/contact-us" rel="noopener">Book your free pool service quote</a> today.</strong></p>
            </div>
            <div class="right col-sm-12 col-lg-5">
              <img width="800" height="640" src="https://i.pinimg.com/736x/ce/db/8e/cedb8ea3e7e0a515edf67cade4465d97.jpg" class="img-fluid" alt="Swim Studs technician brushing a pool during weekly service" />
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="process-wrapper bg-garageup-black">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 class="section-title text-center mb-5">OUR PROCESS</h2>
          <div class="copy-wrapper">
            <div class="process-step">
              <div class="step-number">Step 1</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h3>Request a Free Pool Quote</h3>
                <p>Tell us about your pool size, equipment (chlorine, salt, DE/sand/cartridge), and any concerns. We’ll provide a no-pressure estimate and recommended service plan.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-number">Step 2</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h3>Onboarding & First Visit</h3>
                <p>We inspect equipment, test and balance water, empty baskets, and perform any needed initial cleanup so your pool starts on a clean, healthy baseline.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-number">Step 3</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h3>Weekly Cleaning Routine</h3>
                <p>Each week we skim, brush, and vacuum as needed; test and adjust chemistry; empty skimmer/pump baskets; and check filter pressure and equipment performance.</p>
              </div>
              <div class="step-number">Step 4</div>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h3>Ongoing Monitoring & Support</h3>
                <p>We track trends in water balance, alert you to repair needs, schedule seasonal filter cleans, and leave a service report after every visit—so your pool is always swim‑ready.</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="faq-wrapper">
        <div class="container">
          <h2 class="section-title text-center" style="color: var(--brand-red);">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
          <div class="accordion accordion-flush" id="accordionFlushExample">
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h3 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#flush-collapse-0" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="flush-collapse-0">
                  What does weekly pool cleaning include?
                </button>
              </h3>
              <div id="flush-collapse-0" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                <div class="accordion-body"><p>Our weekly service includes skimming the surface, brushing walls and tile line, vacuuming as needed, emptying skimmer and pump baskets, backwashing or checking filter pressure, testing and balancing water chemistry, and a quick equipment inspection.</p></div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h3 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#flush-collapse-1" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="flush-collapse-1">
                  How often should I clean my pool filter?
                </button>
              </h3>
              <div id="flush-collapse-1" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                <div class="accordion-body"><p>It depends on your system and usage. As a rule of thumb: backwash DE/sand filters when pressure rises 8–10 PSI over clean pressure; rinse cartridge filters every 4–6 weeks during peak season and deep-clean quarterly. Our techs monitor pressure each visit and advise when a clean or replacement is due.</p></div>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h3 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button collapsed" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#flush-collapse-2" aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="flush-collapse-2">
                  How long does a pool cleaning visit take?
                </button>
              </h3>
              <div id="flush-collapse-2" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#accordionFlushExample">
                <div class="accordion-body"><p>Most weekly cleanings take 20–45 minutes depending on pool size, condition, debris load, and equipment access. First-time cleanups or green-to-clean services take longer and may require follow-up visits.</p></div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <div class="container mb-5">
        <section class="get-started bg-garageup-primary bg-icon bg-icon-reverse bg-icon--light bg-icon-reverse--light">
          <div class="estimate-prompt">
            <h2 class="section-title">Ready to get started?</h2>
            <p>Contact us for a free onsite estimate within 24 hours.</p>
            <div class="btn-wrapper "><a href="/contact-us" class="btn btn-primary-dark">Contact Us</a></div>
          </div>
        </section>
      </div>
    </main>

